e extended the decline, printing a fresh low at 1.62582 before closing at 1.62873 \u2014 a modest recovery off the lows, but not one that suggests any conviction from the bid side.\n\nThe structure story is worth unpacking carefully. The 1.6501 area, identified as a prior reaction zone with three touches, acted as a ceiling throughout early July, capping multiple recovery attempts and reinforcing the distribution narrative. Each time price nudged toward that region, sellers reasserted themselves, and the subsequent declines grew more decisive. The pair has now descended roughly 300 pips from that zone in a matter of weeks, arriving at the 1.6298 structure support \u2014 a level that has attracted two prior reactions. That the pair is currently sitting almost precisely on this level makes the near-term read particularly interesting. A clean daily close beneath it would represent a meaningful structural break.\n\nBelow the current zone, the next meaningful area of prior interest sits considerably lower, around 1.6204 and then 1.6189, both of which carry three-touch histories and represent the kind of layered support that would likely slow any extended move rather than arrest it outright.\n\nThe H1 picture over the past 24 hours shows a pair that found a floor near 1.6258 during yesterday's European afternoon, consolidated through the overnight session in a tight 30-pip band between roughly 1.6270 and 1.6292, and has drifted back toward the upper end of that range into today's London session. There is no strong impulsive recovery on the hourly \u2014 the price action reads as consolidation within the prevailing downtrend rather than a genuine reversal attempt. The 1.6298\u20131.6300 area is acting as near-term ceiling on the H1, consistent with the broader structure support now functioning as overhead friction.\n\nToday's economic calendar carries no scheduled high-impact events, which means the pair is likely to remain driven by technical flows and broader risk sentiment. The absence of catalysts cuts both ways \u2014 it reduces the probability of a sharp directional break but also means any move that does develop will carry structural rather than fundamental weight.\n\nThe read shifts if price manages a sustained H1 close back above 1.6320, which would suggest the structure support is holding with more conviction and open the door toward a retest of the 1.6380\u20131.6400 area. The bearish thesis would be reinforced on a daily close beneath 1.6280, which would confirm the structure support has given way and bring the lower prior reaction zones into focus.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}